#slide[
  = Lexing <lexing>

  Lexical analysis is the process of converting a stream of characters into a stream of *tokens*.

  - *Tokens*: The smallest meaningful units (Keywords, Identifiers, Literals, Operators).
  - *Regex*: Often used to define token patterns.
  - *Tools*: Flex (C/C++), Logos (Rust), or hand-written scanners for performance.
]
